Full Tag Name: design to meet needs of students who have been marginalized
2023 Description: Indicates whether the school selected the tag design to meet needs of students who have been marginalized: The learning environment identifies circumstances impacting students who have been most marginalized in order to intentionally design innovations that improve experiences and outcomes for those students. (Students who have been marginalized may include: students with learning differences, students in foster care, students in the justice system, students with low academic performance, students from historically disenfranchised racial and cultural groups.)
2022 Description: The learning environment identifies circumstances impacting students who have been most marginalized in order to intentionally design innovations that improve experiences and outcomes for those students. (Students who have been marginalized may include: students with learning differences, students in foster care, students in the justice system, students with low academic performance, students from historically disenfranchised racial and cultural groups.)
2021 Description: The school designs for and with historically marginalized students, with the goal of improving experiences, supports, and outcomes for these students, who may include: students with learning differences, students in foster care, students in the justice system, students with low academic performance, students from historically disenfranchised racial and cultural groups.
2019 Description: The school puts historically marginalized students at the center, with the goal of improving supports and outcomes for these students. Examples of marginalized students include: students with learning differences, students in foster care, students in the justice system, students with low academic performance.
